Imagine right now, that all you can see in your mind, is the colour black. 
Like a room with no light in it at all. Your mind is entirely black. 
Now, imagine an apple. It's a normal Apple, about the size of your fist, in the middle of that black screen.
The Apple is Red. 
Growing from that Red Apple, is a short brown wooden stem, about half the size of your pinky finger, about half the size of your smallest finger, a short brown wooden stem.
Growing from that brown stem on top of the red apple, is a small green leaf.  The green leaf starts as a sprout, it's curled up and small. But the green leaf  grows out and uncurls from the brown wooden stem. 
As it the green leaf grows and uncurls, it eventually finishes it's growth as a fully grown, healthy green leaf - about the size of your palm. Notice how the fully grown green leaf bends downwards ever so slightly due to gravity. 
So imagine that Red Apple, with brown wooden stem, with green leaf. 
Now. We are now going to keep the brown wooden stem, and keep the green leaf. But we are going to remove the red apple. Only the brown stem and green leaf remain. 
Now, replace the ordinary red apple with a diamond, with the wooden stem and the green leaf growing from that diamond.
Make the diamond the colour Red and about the size of your fist. 
Now, imagine cutting the red diamond into the shape of an apple. Notice the surface of the red diamond, how it is shiny, almost transparent, and now crafted into the shape of an apple.
You now have a red apple-shaped diamond, with wooden stem and green leaf. 
Now, imagine rotating that entire object (apple-diamond, stem and leaf) together as painfully slowly as you can. Control the spin. As slowly as you can.
Notice as the surface of the red apple-diamond gives off light as it rotates slowly - like a disco-ball. 
Now, increase the speed of the spinnning apple-diamond, stem and leaf.  The spin is slow, but faster than before and smooth. 
Notice how the leaf changes where it is pointing as the apple spins in place. Notice how the surface of the apple-diamond gives off light a bit faster. 
Now, spin the apple-diamond faster and faster. Now it is spinning so fast it is blurry.  Notice what it does to the leaf and the light coming off the surface of the apple-diamond.
And stop.  
The question is 1) was it difficult to see everything I decribed? 
2) if it was effortless to see everything I described, was it difficult to stop your brain from imagining more than what was described? 
For example, did you see a worm coming out of the apple, or an entire orchard of apple trees? 
If you saw absolutely nothing at all, then you have Aphantasia. Aphantasia is the inability to generate images in your head. 
If trying to see the objects in your head was a challenge or a strain, then you have Hypo-phantasia. Hypo-phantasia is a difficulty or delay with image generation in your head. 
If seeing everything that was described was almost effortless, then you have Phantasia. Phantasia or near-effortless and compliant image generation is what about 60% of the population has. 
However, if seeing what was described was effortless, and you saw more than what was described without trying, then you have Hyper-phantasia. Hyperphantasia is characterised by effortless and involuntary image generation.  
